    <h1>Biography: Sachin Tendulkar</h1>
    <h2>Early Life</h2>
    <p align="center"><b>Sachin Tendulkar</b> was born on <i>April 24, 1973</i>, in <u>Mumbai, India</u>.<br> Developed an interest in cricket at a young age and trained under coach Ramakant Achrekar.<br>His dedication and passion for the sport were evident from his childhood.</p>
    <h2>Achievements</h2>
    <p align="center">Widely regarded as the <u>greatest batsman</u> in the history of cricket, Sachin has numerous records to his name. <br>He was the first cricketer to score 100 international centuries and has over 34,000 international runs. <br>He played a major role in India's victory in the 2011 Cricket World Cup.</p>
